com.icodici.universa.contract.roles

Class RoleLink

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.icodici.universa.contract.roles.Role
      • com.icodici.universa.contract.roles.RoleLink
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    net.sergeych.biserializer.BiSerializable

    public class RoleLink
extends Role
    A symlink-like role delegate. It uses a named role in the context of a bound Contract (with Role.setContract(Contract) call), then it delegates all actual work to the target role from the contract roles.

    This is used to assign roles to roles, and to create special roles for permissions, etc.

    • Constructor Detail

      • RoleLink

        public RoleLink(java.lang.String name,
                java.lang.String roleName)
        Create a link to a named role. Note that such links can be created ahead of time, e.g. when there is no bound contract or the target role does not yet exist. Just be sure to bind the contract with Role.setContract(Contract) before using the instance.
        Parameters:
        name - new role name
        roleName - existing role name

        public boolean equalKeys(Role otherRole)
        Description copied from class: Role
        A role has exactly same set of keys as in the supplied role. It does not check the logik, only that list of all keys is exactly same.
